<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1028,1775]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,275,1352,1378]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" box="[284,564,1352,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[284,564,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">Pterostichus marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from southern 
<collectingRegion box="[917,1017,1352,1378]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
but has been forgotten since its description and treated as 
<emphasis box="[419,577,1388,1414]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">incertae sedis</emphasis>
in the Palaearctic Catalogue (
<bibRefCitation author="Bousquet, Y." box="[915,1091,1388,1414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" pagination="1810" refId="ref5615" refString="Bousquet, Y. (2003) Tribe Pterostichini Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Archostemata-Myxophaga-Adephaga. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 469 - 520." type="book chapter" year="2003">Bousquet 2003</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bousquet, Y." box="[1101,1163,1388,1414]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" pagination="1810" refId="ref5666" refString="Bousquet, Y. (2017) Tribe Pterostichini Bonelli, 1810. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Archostemata-Myxophaga-Adephaga. Brill, Leiden, Boston, pp. 675 - 755." type="book chapter" year="2017">2017</bibRefCitation>
). Our comparison of the 
<typeStatus box="[151,251,1425,1451]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" box="[290,447,1425,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[290,447,1425,1450]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with a photo of a female 
<typeStatus box="[742,841,1425,1451]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Berlov &amp; Berlov" authorityYear="1997" box="[880,1057,1424,1450]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wellschmiedi">
<emphasis box="[880,1057,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. wellschmiedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kirschenhofer, E." box="[1072,1306,1424,1451]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" pagination="221 - 231" refId="ref6265" refString="Kirschenhofer, E. (1985) Zweineue Pterostichus - Arten aus Sachalin: Pterostichus (Steropus) sachalinensis sp. n. und Pterostichus (Lyperopherus) wellschmiedi sp. n. Entomofauna, 6, 221 - 231." type="journal article" year="1985">Kirschenhofer 1985</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 9) and with specimens treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Berlov &amp; Berlov" authorityYear="1997" box="[447,624,1460,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wellschmiedi">
<emphasis box="[447,624,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. wellschmiedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Berlov &amp; Berlov" authorityYear="1997" box="[781,957,1460,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wellschmiedi">
<emphasis box="[781,957,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. wellschmiedi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Matsumura" authorityYear="1911" box="[1148,1304,1461,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marginatus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1304,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. marginatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, comparison of this 
<collectingRegion box="[368,468,1496,1522]" country="Russia" name="Sakhalin" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">Sakhalin</collectingRegion>
species with 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Morita" authorityYear="1995" box="[621,778,1496,1522]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrugosus">
<emphasis box="[621,778,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. subrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[846,959,1496,1522]" country="Japan" name="Hokkaido" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">Hokkaidô</collectingRegion>
revealed the relationship between the two taxa. Although the previously reported differences in external characters between the two (e.g., flatter elytra with less frequently interrupted intervals, and the absence of metallic luster of dorsal surface in 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Morita" authorityYear="1995" box="[1181,1339,1568,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrugosus">
<emphasis box="[1181,1339,1568,1594]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. subrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Y. N." pageId="4" pageNumber="420" pagination="480 - 503" refId="ref7125" refString="Sundukov, Y. N. (2005) A review of species of the subgenus Lenapterus (Coleoptera, Carabidae, Pterostichus) with description of new species and subspecies from the Sikhote-Alin Mountains. Entomological Review, 85 (5), 480 - 503." type="journal article" year="2005">Sundukov 2005</bibRefCitation>
) were confirmed, no conspicuous differences were found in the structure of the endophallus. Thus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Morita" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrugosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. subrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is downgraded from a distinct species to subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sasakawa &amp; Berlov &amp; Okuzaki" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName=": Straneo" baseAuthorityYear="1955" box="[881,1174,1640,1666]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="marginatus" status="stat. nov." subSpecies="subrugosus">
<emphasis box="[881,1174,1640,1666]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. marginatus subrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1181,1290,1640,1666]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1181,1290,1640,1666]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">stat. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
This species was recorded from the summit of Mt. Rishiri-dake based on two female specimens (
<bibRefCitation author="Morita, S." box="[1115,1262,1676,1703]" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref6725" refString="Morita, S. (1995) Carabid beetles of the Island of Rishiri-to off northern Hokkaido, northeast Japan. Rishiri Studies, 15, 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1995">Morita 1995</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Morita" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Pterostichus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="420" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subrugosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="420">P. subrugosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, the subspecies identity of the Rishiri population remains undetermined because specimens from the locality were not examined in this study.
</paragraph>
